Bug 3666: CodeCompletion - Hungry code assist (1GDRYW5)
jkca (5/15/2001 11:04:56 AM)

jresdk 106
Under certain circumstances, the code assist feature consumes excessive code. To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:

1. Code is changed to: baz(x.foo().foo())
2. The expected code should be: baz(x.foo()x.foo())

public class X {
  void bar(X x) {
    baz(x.foo());
  }

  int foo() {
    return 5;
  }

  void baz(int i, int j) {
  }
}

